page.title: 03Swainsthorpe
page.content: Swainsthorpe covers 2000 acres of land and the population is around 350. Most of the people are in the younger generation because of the new houses that have been built. There are only a few school children in the village. Most people have jobs in Norwich except the farmworkers and some people who make furniture in the village. There are hardly any shops or amenities in the village. The one shop is run by the garage. It sells necessary products. There are no clubs for chilkdren in the village, but for the adults there are bowls, darts, and the Ladies Open Door Club. There is one famous person associated with the village* Sir Alfred Munnings the amous artist.
